WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:06.180
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

01:32.353 --> 01:33.136
-HEY!

01:33.267 --> 01:34.398
THAT'S MY BOAT.

01:34.529 --> 01:36.226
HEY, WHAT DO THOSE GUYS
THINK THEY'RE DOING?

01:36.357 --> 01:37.227
-WOMAN: HEY, COME BACK!

01:37.358 --> 01:38.489
-HEY, COME BACK HERE!

01:38.620 --> 01:41.275
[YELLING]

01:41.405 --> 01:44.321
-WAIT, GET BACK HERE!

01:45.757 --> 01:47.716
-WELL, GUESS WE SWIM.

01:47.846 --> 01:49.196
-SON OF A! [SPLASH]

01:49.326 --> 01:53.156
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

01:57.334 --> 02:00.859
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

02:00.990 --> 02:04.689
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

02:04.820 --> 02:08.737
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

02:08.866 --> 02:12.480
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

02:12.610 --> 02:15.570
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

02:15.700 --> 02:18.312
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALRIGHT

02:20.836 --> 02:23.055
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

02:23.186 --> 02:26.755
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

02:29.627 --> 02:33.414
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

02:33.544 --> 02:35.590
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

02:35.720 --> 02:37.592
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

02:37.722 --> 02:40.943
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:41.073 --> 02:43.641
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

02:43.772 --> 02:47.123
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

03:04.749 --> 03:05.663
-MORNING.

03:06.403 --> 03:08.057
-GOOD MORNING.

03:08.188 --> 03:09.711
-WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE SO EARLY?

03:09.841 --> 03:11.843
-WELL, I ENTERED A
10K RACE NEXT MONTH,

03:11.974 --> 03:13.497
I THOUGHT I BETTER
GET READY FOR IT

03:13.628 --> 03:14.455
-HEY, GOOD FOR YOU!

03:14.585 --> 03:15.847
-YEAH, YOU KNOW,

03:16.370 --> 03:19.155
I WAS LOOKING OVER THE SCHEDULE
AND I HAPPENED TO NOTICE

03:19.286 --> 03:21.375
THAT YOU HAVE
OFF THIS WEEKEND.

03:21.505 --> 03:22.898
-THAT'S RIGHT.

03:23.028 --> 03:24.900
-YEAH, SO YOU PLANNING
A LITTLE HOLIDAY?

03:25.030 --> 03:26.945
MAYBE ONE OF YOUR FAMOUS
FORAYS INTO MEXICO.

03:27.076 --> 03:28.817
-NOW WAIT A MINUTE.

03:28.947 --> 03:30.079
WHY ARE YOU SO INTERESTED IN
WHAT I'M DOING THIS WEEKEND?

03:30.210 --> 03:31.602
-I'M NOT.

03:31.733 --> 03:32.995
I JUST, YOU KNOW, I
MIGHT NEED A FAVOR.

03:33.125 --> 03:33.952
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN,

03:34.083 --> 03:35.040
YOU MIGHT NEED A FAVOR?

03:35.171 --> 03:36.564
EITHER YOU DO OR YOU DON'T,

03:36.694 --> 03:38.000
YOU DON'T JUST
"MIGHT" NEED A FAVOR.

03:38.130 --> 03:39.219
MY BEST FRIEND IS GETTING
MARRIED THIS SATURDAY.

03:39.349 --> 03:40.437
-AND YOU NEED A DATE.

03:40.568 --> 03:42.831
-NO, THIS IS NOT A DATE.

03:42.961 --> 03:43.919
-THEN WHAT IS IT?

03:44.528 --> 03:45.529
-A FAVOR.

03:45.660 --> 03:47.009
-AH, SATURDAY,
I'M NOT SO SURE.

03:47.139 --> 03:48.271
THAT'S AWFULLY
SHORT NOTICE.

03:48.924 --> 03:51.796
-LOOK, I REALIZE YOU LEAD
A VERY ACTIVE SOCIAL LIFE.

03:51.927 --> 03:53.624
-ON THE OTHER HAND, WE
CAN'T HAVE YOU GOING SOLO

03:53.755 --> 03:55.235
TO YOUR BEST FRIEND'S
WEDDING, NOW CAN WE?

03:55.365 --> 03:57.280
-IT'S NOT THAT HE
MINDS, IT'S JUST.

03:57.411 --> 03:58.194
-HE?

03:58.325 --> 03:59.891
YOUR BEST FRIEND'S THE GROOM?

04:00.022 --> 04:01.893
-WHY IS THAT SO UNUSUAL?

04:02.024 --> 04:04.244
WHAT, YOU THINK A MAN AND A
WOMAN CAN'T HAVE A RELATIONSHIP

04:04.374 --> 04:06.071
WITHOUT THERE BEING A
PHYSICAL ATTRACTION?

04:06.202 --> 04:08.639
-WELL I THINK IT'S POSSIBLE,
BUT INCREDIBLY RARE.

04:08.770 --> 04:10.598
-NO, TRUST ME, SAM AND
I ARE BEST FRIENDS.

04:10.728 --> 04:12.077
I HAVE KNOWN
HIM SINCE COLLEGE.

04:12.208 --> 04:14.210
-UH, WOULD YOU UH...

04:15.559 --> 04:16.603
THANK YOU.

04:16.733 --> 04:17.866
SO, IF HE'S YOUR
BEST FRIEND,

04:17.995 --> 04:19.607
THEN WHY ISN'T
HE MARRYING YOU?

04:19.737 --> 04:21.130
-WHAT KIND OF A
QUESTION IS THAT?

04:21.261 --> 04:22.087
-UH, TOO PERSONAL?

04:22.218 --> 04:23.001
-A TAD.

04:23.132 --> 04:24.525
-SORRY.

04:24.655 --> 04:26.309
-LISTEN, THE RECEPTION'S
AT THE BELLER BAY CLUB,

04:26.440 --> 04:28.137
IT'S ON THE SAND, YOU WILL
FEEL COMPLETELY AT HOME,

04:28.268 --> 04:29.486
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

04:29.617 --> 04:30.922
-WELL IT SOUNDS
AWFULLY TEMPTING, BUT--

04:31.053 --> 04:32.533
-BUCHANAN, YOU OWE ME.

04:32.663 --> 04:33.664
-WHAT DO YOU
MEAN, I OWE YOU?

04:33.795 --> 04:34.839
I OWE YOU FOR WHAT?

04:34.970 --> 04:36.101
-IT DOESN'T
MATTER FOR WHAT,

04:36.232 --> 04:37.015
I'M COUNTING ON YOU.

04:37.146 --> 04:38.539
I NEED BACKUP HERE.

04:38.669 --> 04:40.105
-ALRIGHT, I'LL
TELL YOU WHAT,

04:40.236 --> 04:43.370
I'LL CHECK MY SCHEDULE
AND GET BACK TO YOU.

04:43.500 --> 04:45.328
-AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

04:48.940 --> 04:50.115
PLEASE.

04:51.552 --> 04:52.857
[SIGHS]

05:00.125 --> 05:04.695
-[DREAMY MUSIC]

05:10.484 --> 05:11.528
-HEY, ALEX.

05:13.051 --> 05:14.575
-WOULD YOU LOOK AT THIS?

05:14.705 --> 05:16.098
-THAT THING'S GREAT!

05:17.055 --> 05:18.883
-IT'S STRANGE.

05:19.014 --> 05:21.321
-WHAT'S SO STRANGE ABOUT
A SAND CASTLE ON THE BEACH?

05:23.105 --> 05:25.716
-BECAUSE I WAS THE ONE WHO
CLOSED THIS TOWER LAST NIGHT,

05:25.847 --> 05:28.415
IT IS 6:45AM.

05:29.198 --> 05:31.243
WHO WOULD BUILD A
CASTLE IN THE DARK?

05:32.070 --> 05:33.202
YOU KNOW?

05:33.333 --> 05:34.551
-THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

05:35.770 --> 05:36.771
-SEE YA!

05:36.901 --> 05:38.076
-HAVE FUN.

05:40.557 --> 05:44.605
-[DREAMY MUSIC]

05:53.614 --> 05:55.398
-I ALREADY GAVE YOU A
DESCRIPTION OF THE VESSEL,

05:55.529 --> 05:56.965
DIDN'T YOU WRITE IT DOWN?

05:57.966 --> 05:59.881
I REALIZE YOU'RE JUST
TRYING TO DO YOUR JOB!

06:01.143 --> 06:02.666
I WILL TRY NOT TO
RAISE MY VOICE.

06:02.797 --> 06:04.581
I WILL EVEN
WHISPER IF YOU LIKE.

06:04.712 --> 06:06.235
-WHO'S HE TALKING TO?

06:06.366 --> 06:08.280
-HARBOR PATROL, SOMEONE
STOLE HIS BOAT YESTERDAY.

06:08.411 --> 06:09.891
-YOU'RE KIDDING.

06:10.021 --> 06:12.110
-DO I MIND IF YOU
PUT ME ON HOLD?

06:12.241 --> 06:13.547
DO I HAVE ANY CHOICE?

06:14.809 --> 06:15.723
-CODY, I'M REALLY SORRY.

06:15.853 --> 06:17.420
THAT'S TERRIBLE.

06:17.551 --> 06:19.161
-NO, NO, NO, WHAT'S WORSE
IS THE AFTER EFFECTS.

06:19.291 --> 06:21.468
DEALING WITH THESE PAPER
PUSHERS, FILLING OUT THE FORMS.

06:21.598 --> 06:23.295
FEELS LIKE I'M GOING TO BE ON
HOLD FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE!

06:23.426 --> 06:25.385
-[PHONE RINGS]

06:25.515 --> 06:26.777
-I'LL GET IT.

06:28.475 --> 06:29.389
HELLO?

06:29.998 --> 06:31.347
-HI, AL, IT'S ME, SAM!

06:31.478 --> 06:32.783
-HEY HANDSOME, WHAT'S UP?

06:32.914 --> 06:34.481
YOU STARTING TO
LOSE YOUR NERVE?

06:34.611 --> 06:36.265
-ARE YOU KIDDING, I CAN
HARDLY WAIT UNTIL SATURDAY.

06:36.396 --> 06:37.832
WAIT UNTIL YOU MEET HER.

06:37.962 --> 06:40.051
I HAVE NEVER FELT THIS
WAY BEFORE ABOUT ANYONE.

06:40.182 --> 06:41.879
IT'S TORTURE JUST
BEING AWAY FROM HER.

06:42.010 --> 06:43.925
-WELL, I'M SURE SHE'S
ABSOLUTELY LOVELY.

06:44.055 --> 06:45.143
BUT TELL ME,
HOW ARE YOU?

06:45.274 --> 06:46.623
-I NEED YOUR HELP.

06:46.754 --> 06:48.669
I AM STUCK IN NEW
YORK UNTIL FRIDAY.

06:48.799 --> 06:50.584
I'M ACTUALLY ON
THE FDR RIGHT NOW.

06:50.714 --> 06:52.847
DIANE'S GONNA GET
INTO LA TOMORROW.

06:52.977 --> 06:54.239
SHE DOESN'T KNOW A SOUL,

06:54.370 --> 06:55.589
I WAS HOPING YOU
COULD SHOW HER AROUND.

06:55.719 --> 06:58.461
-YEAH, SURE, YOU KNOW,

06:58.592 --> 06:59.462
I'LL DO ANYTHING FOR YOU,

06:59.593 --> 07:01.333
YOU KNOW THAT.

07:01.464 --> 07:02.422
DON'T YOU THINK SHE'S GONNA
FEEL A LITTLE UNCOMFORTABLE

07:02.552 --> 07:03.597
WITH A COMPLETE STRANGER?

07:03.727 --> 07:04.641
-YOU'RE NO STRANGER, AL.

07:04.772 --> 07:06.077
I'VE TOLD HER
ALL ABOUT YOU,

07:06.208 --> 07:07.078
SHE CAN'T WAIT
TO MEET YOU.

07:07.209 --> 07:08.863
-[TRUCK HONKS]

07:08.993 --> 07:10.430
-SO LISTEN, SHE GETS TO THE
AIRPORT AT FOUR O'CLOCK.

07:10.560 --> 07:12.475
I'LL JUST TELL HER TO GO
STRAIGHT TO THE BEACH.

07:13.128 --> 07:14.564
AL, THANKS A MILLION.

07:14.695 --> 07:15.522
-YEAH.

07:15.652 --> 07:17.175
I'LL SEE YOU ON
FRIDAY, OKAY?

07:17.698 --> 07:18.742
BYE.

07:20.483 --> 07:21.397
[SIGHS]

07:25.183 --> 07:29.187
-[PEACEFUL DREAMY MUSIC]

07:57.999 --> 08:00.567
-NO, NO, NO, I HAVE
A $500 DEDUCTIBLE.

08:01.524 --> 08:03.439
I'M HOLDING THE POLICY
RIGHT IN MY HAND!

08:04.048 --> 08:05.528
-SORRY.

08:05.659 --> 08:06.921
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN THAT
DOESN'T COVER THEFT?

08:08.618 --> 08:09.967
NO, I HAVEN'T SPOKEN
TO THE ADJUSTER YET,

08:10.098 --> 08:11.621
HE HASN'T RETURNED MY CALL.

08:11.752 --> 08:12.666
-HANG IN THERE, BUDDY.

08:12.796 --> 08:13.623
-NO, I KNOW THAT.

08:13.754 --> 08:15.146
-EXCUSE ME.

08:15.277 --> 08:16.191
HAVE YOU NOTICED ANYONE
BUILDING SANDCASTLES

08:16.321 --> 08:18.106
ON THE BEACH LATELY?

08:18.236 --> 08:19.673
-YEAH, JUST ABOUT EVERY KID
THAT COMES DOWN TO THE BEACH.

08:19.803 --> 08:20.935
-NO, I'M TALKING ABOUT
REALLY GOOD ONES,

08:21.065 --> 08:22.414
PROFESSIONAL ONES.

08:22.545 --> 08:23.459
IS THERE A CONTEST
COMING UP OR SOMETHING?

08:24.025 --> 08:24.852
-NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

08:24.982 --> 08:25.766
-HEY, ALEX?

08:25.896 --> 08:26.767
-YEAH.

08:27.289 --> 08:28.246
-SOMEONE HERE TO SEE YOU.

08:28.377 --> 08:29.160
WAITING OUTSIDE.

08:29.291 --> 08:30.074
-ALRIGHT.

08:30.205 --> 08:30.988
SEE YOU, NEWMIE.

08:31.119 --> 08:32.033
-SEE YOU.

08:36.558 --> 08:41.129
-[INQUISITIVE MUSIC]

09:00.757 --> 09:01.889
-UH, DIANE?

09:02.019 --> 09:03.760
-ALEX, HI!

09:03.891 --> 09:04.848
THIS IS GREAT.

09:05.457 --> 09:06.850
EVER SINCE I MET SAM,

09:06.981 --> 09:08.939
ALL I'VE HEARD IS
ALEX THIS, ALEX THAT.

09:09.070 --> 09:10.158
I FEEL LIKE I
ALREADY KNOW YOU.

09:10.288 --> 09:11.638
-REALLY?

09:11.768 --> 09:12.769
-HE SAID YOU
WERE THE STANDARD

09:12.900 --> 09:13.857
BY WHICH HE JUDGED
ALL OTHER WOMEN.

09:13.988 --> 09:15.642
-WELL I'M SURE
HE WAS JOKING.

09:15.772 --> 09:17.208
-OH?

09:17.339 --> 09:18.775
-LISTEN, HE TOLD ME
TO SHOW YOU AROUND.

09:18.906 --> 09:19.950
IS THERE ANYTHING SPECIAL
YOU WANNA SEE OR DO?

09:20.081 --> 09:21.561
-I WAS HOPING WE
COULD JUST HANG OUT

09:21.691 --> 09:22.605
AROUND HERE FOR A WHILE.

09:22.736 --> 09:24.651
[LAUGHS] I'M FROM KANSAS CITY,

09:24.781 --> 09:26.000
I'VE NEVER BEEN TO
THE BEACH BEFORE.

09:26.130 --> 09:27.349
-YOU KNOW WHAT,
I'M FROM ST. LOUIS,

09:27.479 --> 09:28.611
I KNOW EXACTLY HOW YOU FEEL.

09:28.742 --> 09:30.134
-EVERYTHING'S SO BEAUTIFUL!

09:30.265 --> 09:32.659
THE WATER, THE SAND,

09:33.442 --> 09:34.704
THE PEOPLE. [LAUGHS]

09:34.835 --> 09:36.184
WHAT A PLACE TO WORK!

09:36.314 --> 09:38.578
-WELL, BEST OFFICE IN
THE WORLD, AS THEY SAY.

09:39.187 --> 09:40.884
-SAM PROMISED WE'D GET A
HOUSE RIGHT ON THE WATER.

09:41.015 --> 09:42.364
-REALLY?

09:42.494 --> 09:43.800
WOW, HE MUST BE
DOING PRETTY WELL.

09:43.931 --> 09:46.237
-SAM'S THE MOST REMARKABLE
PERSON I'VE EVER MET.

09:46.368 --> 09:48.805
THE MOMENT I LAID
EYES ON HIM I KNEW

09:48.936 --> 09:51.112
HE WAS THE MAN I WAS GONNA
SPEND THE REST OF MY LIFE WITH.

09:52.766 --> 09:53.767
-ALEX: HM.

09:58.075 --> 09:58.989
-WHO'S THAT?

10:00.556 --> 10:02.253
-THAT'S MITCH BUCHANAN.

10:02.384 --> 10:04.386
HE'S SORT OF THE COMMANDER
IN CHIEF HERE AT BAYWATCH.

10:08.216 --> 10:09.260
-HEY, HI.

10:09.391 --> 10:10.653
-DIANE: HI.
-ALEX: HI.

10:11.698 --> 10:14.004
-DIANE, THIS IS
MITCH BUCHANAN,

10:14.135 --> 10:15.266
MITCH, THIS IS DIANE.

10:15.397 --> 10:16.267
-NICE TO MEET YOU.

10:16.398 --> 10:18.182
-NICE TO MEET YOU, MITCH.

10:18.313 --> 10:19.662
-OH, YOU'RE THE DIANE THAT'S
MARRYING ALEX'S BEST FRIEND.

10:19.793 --> 10:20.924
-YEAH, I WAS PLANNING TO.

10:21.882 --> 10:23.710
I MEAN YES, I AM.

10:23.840 --> 10:24.624
-MITCH: WELL GOOD.

10:24.754 --> 10:25.537
CONGRATULATIONS.

10:25.668 --> 10:26.756
-THANK YOU.

10:26.887 --> 10:28.105
-MAN: HEY, MITCH!

10:28.236 --> 10:29.193
-UH, EXCUSE ME, I GOTTA GO.

10:29.324 --> 10:30.107
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

10:30.238 --> 10:31.413
-I CERTAINLY HOPE SO.

10:31.543 --> 10:32.632
-BYE!

10:35.896 --> 10:37.288
[LAUGHS]

10:40.727 --> 10:45.514
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

10:53.653 --> 10:57.526
-[GIRLS CHATTER]

11:12.933 --> 11:13.847
-HEY, ALEX.

11:13.977 --> 11:15.109
-HELLO!

11:18.025 --> 11:18.895
HOW'RE YOU DOING?

11:19.026 --> 11:20.288
-GOOD.

11:21.724 --> 11:23.683
BETTER POUR SOME COLD
WATER ON THOSE TWO, HUH?

11:23.813 --> 11:26.033
-YEAH, WAS JUST THINKING
THE SAME THING MYSELF.

11:26.163 --> 11:27.817
-SO, HOW'D IT GO LAST
NIGHT WITH DIANE?

11:27.948 --> 11:29.036
-NOT GOOD.

11:29.166 --> 11:30.733
-NOT GOOD, WHAT HAPPENED?

11:30.864 --> 11:33.605
OH, DON'T TELL ME, YOU'RE
NOT JEALOUS, ARE YOU?

11:34.171 --> 11:35.564
-WHY WOULD I BE JEALOUS?

11:35.695 --> 11:37.261
-BECAUSE SHE'S MARRYING
YOUR BEST FRIEND.

11:37.392 --> 11:39.176
-[SIGHS] THAT IS
NOT THE PROBLEM.

11:39.307 --> 11:40.264
-THEN WHAT IS?

11:40.830 --> 11:42.702
-SHE'S IN LOVE
WITH ANOTHER MAN.

11:43.354 --> 11:44.312
-WHO?

11:44.442 --> 11:45.356
-YOU.

11:46.009 --> 11:47.228
-ME?

11:47.358 --> 11:48.577
-DON'T TELL ME
YOU DIDN'T NOTICE.

11:48.708 --> 11:49.796
SHE'S GOT A MAD
CRUSH ON YOU, MITCH.

11:50.535 --> 11:51.319
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

11:51.449 --> 11:52.929
-NO!

11:53.060 --> 11:53.843
I MEAN, I TAKE HER OUT
TO DINNER LAST NIGHT,

11:53.974 --> 11:54.975
WE WENT TO BEAU RIVAGE,

11:55.105 --> 11:56.628
ALL SHE DID WAS
ASK ABOUT YOU.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.282
AND THEN THE WAITER
COMES TO THE TABLE

11:58.413 --> 11:59.980
AND ASKS HER
WHAT SHE WANTS,

12:00.110 --> 12:01.590
AND SHE SAYS TO ME,

12:01.721 --> 12:03.635
"WHAT DOES MITCH
USUALLY ORDER?"

12:03.766 --> 12:05.289
-WELL, I HOPE YOU
TOLD HER RACK OF LAMB.

12:05.420 --> 12:07.944
-[SIGH] MITCH,
THIS IS NOT FUNNY.

12:08.075 --> 12:08.989
THIS IS MY BEST FRIEND.

12:09.119 --> 12:10.686
HE'S GONNA BE HEARTBROKEN.

12:18.433 --> 12:20.565
-OH MY GOD, OH GOD!

12:21.566 --> 12:25.832
-[INTENSE MUSIC]

12:28.443 --> 12:29.531
TAMMY?

12:30.097 --> 12:31.272
BETSY?

12:34.623 --> 12:36.668
LIFEGUARD, LIFEGUARD!

12:37.278 --> 12:38.540
HAVE YOU SEEN
TWO LITTLE GIRLS?

12:38.670 --> 12:40.107
THEY WERE PLAYING
RIGHT OVER THERE.

12:40.237 --> 12:41.195
-WELL, THEY MUST BE
AROUND HERE SOMEWHERE,

12:41.325 --> 12:41.848
THEY DIDN'T GO IN THE WATER.

12:41.978 --> 12:43.371
-HOW DO YOU KNOW?

12:43.501 --> 12:44.589
-BECAUSE I WAS
WATCHING THE WATER.

12:44.720 --> 12:45.329
-YOU WERE
TALKING TO HIM.

12:45.460 --> 12:46.853
-ARE YOU THE SISTER?

12:46.983 --> 12:48.419
-GIRL: NO, I'M
THE BABYSITTER.

12:48.550 --> 12:49.769
-THEN YOU SHOULD HAVE
BEEN WATCHING THEM.

12:49.899 --> 12:50.900
-MITCH: WHAT
WERE THEY WEARING?

12:51.422 --> 12:52.815
-TAMMY WAS WEARING BLUE

12:52.946 --> 12:55.339
AND BETSY WAS WEARING
ORANGE AND BLACK.

12:56.601 --> 12:58.125
-WE GOT TWO KIDS,
POSSIBLE KIDNAPPING,

12:58.255 --> 12:59.213
POSSIBLE DROWNING.

12:59.343 --> 13:00.823
SIX AND EIGHT YEARS OLD.

13:00.954 --> 13:02.216
ONE IS WEARING YELLOW,
ONE IS WEARING A HAT.

13:02.346 --> 13:03.086
-WALKIE: TWO?

13:03.217 --> 13:04.087
-YES.

13:04.218 --> 13:05.001
YEAH I'VE SEARCH THEM.

13:05.132 --> 13:06.263
VENICE TO SAN PEDRO.

13:06.394 --> 13:07.134
IF YOU CAN
GET THE CHOPPERS,

13:07.264 --> 13:08.048
GET THEM IN HERE!

13:08.178 --> 13:08.962
-WALKIE: ROGER THAT.

13:09.092 --> 13:09.832
-WE GOTTA FIND THEM.

13:09.963 --> 13:11.703
-WE WILL, WE WILL.

13:11.834 --> 13:13.140
-ALRIGHT, THAT'S IT, THEY
GOTTA CALL FOR A BODY SEARCH.

13:13.270 --> 13:14.228
-I'M TELLING YOU,
THEY ARE NOT OUT THERE.

13:14.358 --> 13:15.055
-WE GOTTA FOLLOW PROCEDURE.

13:15.185 --> 13:16.099
-I KNOW.

13:18.188 --> 13:20.408
-HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:20.538 --> 13:21.713
-TAMMY, BETSY,
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

13:21.844 --> 13:22.932
-WE JUST WENT
TO THE SNACK BAR,

13:23.063 --> 13:24.368
WE TRIED TO TELL YOU.

13:24.499 --> 13:26.414
-BUT YOU WERE BUSY.

13:28.155 --> 13:29.243
-MR. BUCHANAN!

13:30.070 --> 13:31.071
-ARE THESE THE GIRLS?

13:31.201 --> 13:32.289
-YEAH, THEY TURNED UP.

13:32.420 --> 13:33.247
-ARE YOU OKAY?

13:33.377 --> 13:34.814
-YES.

13:34.944 --> 13:37.512
-[SIGH] I HOPE YOU
LEARNED A LESSON HERE.

13:37.642 --> 13:38.774
-I'M SORRY.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.341
-WELL, SORRY'S
NOT GONNA CUT IT,

13:40.471 --> 13:41.690
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO TALK TO THE PARENTS

13:41.821 --> 13:42.473
AND TELL THEM
WHAT HAPPENED.

13:42.604 --> 13:43.823
-BUT I'LL GET FIRED!

13:43.953 --> 13:44.432
-WOULD YOU
RATHER I TELL THEM?

13:45.085 --> 13:46.695
-[SIGH] I'LL DO IT.

13:46.826 --> 13:48.131
-OKAY.

13:50.394 --> 13:51.743
WE FOUND THEM, CALL
THE WHOLE THING OFF,

13:51.874 --> 13:52.701
THAT'S A CODE FOUR.

13:52.832 --> 13:54.050
CODE FOUR.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.009
-WALKIE: ROGER
THAT, CODE FOUR.

13:56.139 --> 13:57.662
-DO YOU WANT A
SLICE OF PIZZA?

13:57.793 --> 13:59.969
IT'S PEPPERONI.

14:00.100 --> 14:01.144
-NO, THANKS, GIRLS.

14:01.275 --> 14:02.624
DO ME A FAVOR.

14:02.754 --> 14:04.844
WOULD YOU STAY CLOSE TO
YOUR BABYSITTER, OKAY?

14:04.974 --> 14:06.193
-OKAY.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.109
-[SIGHS]

14:11.024 --> 14:12.025
-MITCH?

14:12.634 --> 14:13.853
HI.

14:13.983 --> 14:15.289
YOU ALWAYS THIS
COOL UNDER PRESSURE?

14:15.419 --> 14:17.073
-[SIGHS]

14:22.165 --> 14:26.474
-[INTRIGUING MUSIC]

14:30.217 --> 14:31.914
-[MITCH SIGHS]

14:39.835 --> 14:40.662
-DIANE: MITCH?

14:40.792 --> 14:42.011
-OH YEAH, HEY.

14:43.708 --> 14:45.014
-I NEVER KNEW
BEING A LIFEGUARD

14:45.145 --> 14:47.495
REQUIRED HAVING
SO MANY SKILLS.

14:48.583 --> 14:50.106
I THOUGHT YOU JUST HAD
TO BE A GOOD SWIMMER.

14:50.237 --> 14:53.631
-NO, NO, IT'S A LOT MORE
COMPLEX THAN PEOPLE IMAGINE.

14:54.284 --> 14:56.156
-WELL, ALL I CAN SAY IS,

14:56.896 --> 14:58.071
I'M IMPRESSED.

14:58.201 --> 14:59.072
-THANKS.

15:00.595 --> 15:01.901
GETTING READY
FOR THE BIG DAY?

15:02.031 --> 15:03.163
-THE BIG DAY?

15:03.815 --> 15:04.904
-THE WEDDING.

15:06.949 --> 15:08.168
-THAT, UH.

15:09.821 --> 15:10.997
YOU'RE NOT
MARRIED, ARE YOU?

15:11.127 --> 15:14.000
-UM, NO, NOT
AT THE MOMENT.

15:14.130 --> 15:14.914
-ENGAGED?

15:15.044 --> 15:15.827
-DIVORCED.

15:15.958 --> 15:17.873
-OH, SORRY.

15:18.004 --> 15:19.309
I DIDN'T MEAN TO PRY.

15:20.223 --> 15:21.485
IT'S JUST THAT YOU'RE
NOT WEARING A RING.

15:21.616 --> 15:24.140
-LOOK, DIANE, I CAN'T
REALLY CONTINUE.

15:24.271 --> 15:27.709
-IT'S JUST, I'M SO
AMAZED BY WHAT YOU DO.

15:27.839 --> 15:30.146
YOU PUT YOUR LIFE ON
THE LINE EVERY DAY.

15:30.277 --> 15:32.061
YOU'RE A REAL LIFE HERO.

15:32.192 --> 15:33.497
-WHAT I DO IS NO DIFFERENT

15:33.628 --> 15:35.282
THAN WHAT A LOT
OF PEOPLE DO.

15:35.412 --> 15:37.284
I MEAN, FIREMEN AND POLICEMEN,
THEY ALL HELP PEOPLE.

15:37.414 --> 15:38.763
WHAT'S YOUR FIANCE?

15:38.894 --> 15:41.244
-OH, HE'S JUST
A BUSINESSMAN.

15:41.375 --> 15:42.419
-DON'T SAY JUST
A BUSINESSMAN,

15:42.550 --> 15:43.420
THEY'RE VERY IMPORTANT.

15:44.334 --> 15:45.466
THEY HELP A LOT OF PEOPLE.

15:45.596 --> 15:47.468
THEY HELP PEOPLE START
JOBS, OPPORTUNITIES,

15:47.598 --> 15:48.817
THEY HELP PUT
FOOD ON THE TABLE.

15:50.297 --> 15:51.907
-I NEVER THOUGHT
ABOUT IT THAT WAY.

15:52.473 --> 15:54.997
-THEY CAN MAKE A WORLD OF
DIFFERENCE IN PEOPLE'S LIVES.

15:58.653 --> 15:59.523
-YOU'RE VERY SMART.

16:00.437 --> 16:01.438
-THANK YOU.

16:02.787 --> 16:04.528
-WALKIE: AMF 295 TO MITCH.

16:04.659 --> 16:05.747
-BUCHANAN, COME BACK.

16:05.877 --> 16:07.662
-WALKIE: BE ADVISED, MITCH,

16:07.792 --> 16:08.619
WE GOT A STRONG RIP OFF
THE JETTY WITH SWIMMERS IN.

16:08.750 --> 16:09.664
-WHAT'S WRONG?

16:09.794 --> 16:11.144
-AH, I GOT A RIP CURRENT.

16:11.274 --> 16:12.058
LOOK, I GOTTA GET
PEOPLE OUT OF THE WATER.

16:12.188 --> 16:13.407
YOU TAKE CARE, OKAY?

16:22.633 --> 16:27.638
-[BRIGHT ROCK MUSIC]

16:45.004 --> 16:48.050
♪ YOU'RE EVERYBODIES HERO

16:49.747 --> 16:53.621
♪ WORTH MORE THAN SILVER AND GOLD

16:55.405 --> 16:59.192
♪ I CAN'T GET YOU OFF MY MIND

17:00.671 --> 17:04.022
♪ YOU'RE HUMBLE AND YOUR KIND

17:06.199 --> 17:10.029
♪ YOU'RE JUST WHAT I'M LOOKING FOR

17:11.595 --> 17:15.382
♪ THE ONE THAT I ADORE

17:15.512 --> 17:18.124
♪ IT'S UNBELIEVABLE TO YOU

