18:29.978 --> 18:32.067
♪ YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT ♪

18:32.633 --> 18:37.507
♪ DON'T YOU KNOW THAT
YOU'RE SOMETHING AMAZING ♪

18:40.641 --> 18:46.168
♪ YOU'RE AMAZING, YOU'RE AMAZING
SO AMAZING ♪

18:47.126 --> 18:50.694
♪ SO AMAZING

18:57.266 --> 18:58.659
-MITCH: HEY, BUD.
WHAT A DAY, HUH?

18:58.789 --> 18:59.964
BEAU RIVAGE LATER?

19:00.095 --> 19:00.530
-ALEX: HEY, MITCH.
CAN WE TALK?

19:00.661 --> 19:02.358
-SURE.

19:02.489 --> 19:03.707
WE REALLY GOTTA NIP THIS
DIANE SITUATION IN THE BUD.

19:03.838 --> 19:05.100
-YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.

19:06.014 --> 19:07.363
-YOU'RE ACTUALLY
AGREEING WITH ME?

19:08.234 --> 19:10.061
-SHE WAS AT MY
TOWER THE ENTIRE DAY.

19:10.192 --> 19:11.367
-I KNOW!

19:11.498 --> 19:12.890
SHE IS A COMPLETE
BASKET CASE.

19:13.021 --> 19:14.979
HOWEVER, I THINK I HAVE
COME UP WITH A PLAN

19:15.110 --> 19:15.937
TO BRING HER
BACK TO REALITY.

19:16.067 --> 19:17.547
-GOOD.

19:17.678 --> 19:18.548
-I TOLD HER YOU WERE GAY.
-YOU DID NOT.

19:18.679 --> 19:19.723
-I'M KIDDING!

19:19.854 --> 19:21.029
I ACTUALLY TOLD HER
WE WERE A COUPLE.

19:21.160 --> 19:22.378
-WHAT?

19:22.509 --> 19:23.814
-AND THAT YOU WERE
KEEPING IT A SECRET

19:23.945 --> 19:25.338
BECAUSE YOU
PROMISED THE CHIEF

19:25.468 --> 19:26.861
THAT YOU WOULDN'T DATE
LIFEGUARDS ANYMORE.

19:26.991 --> 19:28.558
-WHY DON'T YOU JUST
TELL HER THE TRUTH?

19:28.689 --> 19:30.038
-BECAUSE, SHE CAN'T
HANDLE THE TRUTH.

19:30.169 --> 19:31.779
SHE'S WALKING AROUND
IN A DREAM WORLD.

19:31.909 --> 19:33.911
-NO, YOU'RE WALKING
AROUND IN A DREAM WORLD.

19:34.042 --> 19:37.088
-MITCH, THE WOMAN WORSHIPS
THE SAND YOU WALK ON.

19:37.698 --> 19:39.003
BESIDES, I COULDN'T
THINK OF ANOTHER PLAN.

19:39.134 --> 19:40.875
SO I'LL SEE YOU
AROUND SEVEN?

19:41.789 --> 19:43.356
-WHAT'S AT SEVEN?

19:43.486 --> 19:44.357
-WELL, I INVITED DIANE
TO YOUR HOUSE FOR DINNER.

19:44.487 --> 19:45.836
-NO, RYKER, NO.

19:45.967 --> 19:47.229
-WOULD YOU FIX
SOMETHING LIGHT

19:47.360 --> 19:48.317
BECAUSE I'VE BEEN
SNACKING ALL DAY.

19:48.448 --> 19:49.710
-THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

19:49.840 --> 19:51.233
-I'M KIDDING.
I'LL GO TO THE DELI.

19:51.364 --> 19:52.756
-NO, FORGET IT, YOU'RE
OUT OF YOUR MIND.

19:52.887 --> 19:54.062
-HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
THIS IS NOT MY FAULT.

19:54.193 --> 19:55.019
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT'S
SO IRRESISTIBLE.

19:55.150 --> 19:56.499
-[MITCH GROANS]

20:08.076 --> 20:09.512
-[MAN MOANS]

20:15.431 --> 20:17.868
-MAN: COME ON,
YOU CAN DO IT.

20:20.131 --> 20:23.134
COME ON, COME ON,

20:23.700 --> 20:24.658
YOU CAN DO IT.

20:24.788 --> 20:26.007
-ALEX: CODY?
-HUH?

20:26.137 --> 20:27.748
-ARE YOU OKAY?
-OH YEAH.

20:28.966 --> 20:30.577
-ARE YOU STILL
ON THE PHONE?

20:30.707 --> 20:32.883
-YEAH. I'M ON
HOLD, STILL. [LAUGHS]

20:33.014 --> 20:34.885
-YOU HAGGLING WITH THE
INSURANCE COMPANY STILL?

20:35.016 --> 20:36.365
-OH NO, THIS
IS THE POLICE.

20:36.496 --> 20:37.758
YOU SEE THAT REPORT
I FILLED OUT,

20:37.888 --> 20:39.107
THEY SEEM TO
HAVE MISPLACED.

20:39.238 --> 20:41.457
-[SIGHS] ARE YOU
FRUSTRATED OR WHAT?

20:41.588 --> 20:42.980
-WHY SHOULD
I BE FRUSTRATED?

20:43.111 --> 20:44.895
JUST BECAUSE I SANK
EVER DIME I HAD

20:45.026 --> 20:46.375
INTO A BOAT I'LL
NEVER SEE AGAIN,

20:46.506 --> 20:48.464
I MEAN, HEY, WHAT'S
THE BIG DEAL, YOU KNOW?

20:48.595 --> 20:49.422
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT THE
GOOD THING IS, ALEX?

20:49.552 --> 20:50.945
DO YOU?

20:51.075 --> 20:52.686
I'M NOT GONNA LET
THEM GET TO ME.

20:52.816 --> 20:53.687
NO WAY.

20:54.253 --> 20:55.210
-I'M GLAD YOU'RE
GONNA SURVIVE.

20:55.341 --> 20:56.255
-AND SOMETHING ELSE.

20:56.385 --> 20:57.343
WHEN I GET THROUGH THIS,

20:58.300 --> 20:59.736
I'M GONNA FIX MY LOCKER.

21:03.218 --> 21:05.002
MUSIC STILL. [LAUGHS]

21:05.612 --> 21:06.482
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

21:07.396 --> 21:09.137
DID YOU EVER FIND THAT
MYSTERIOUS SANDCASTLE BUILDER?

21:09.268 --> 21:10.225
-NO.

21:10.356 --> 21:11.487
-HM.

21:12.009 --> 21:13.228
DO YOU THINK HE'S STILL
DOING THEM AT NIGHT?

21:13.968 --> 21:16.057
-WELL, NOBODY'S REPORTED
ANYTHING DURING THE DAY.

21:16.187 --> 21:16.971
-HELLO!

21:17.101 --> 21:17.885
OH NO.

21:18.015 --> 21:18.929
MORE MUSIC.

21:19.060 --> 21:20.061
YOU KNOW WHAT?

21:21.280 --> 21:22.803
WHAT'S YOUR
THEORY ON THIS?

21:23.543 --> 21:25.458
I MEAN, ALIENS
WITH NIGHT VISION?

21:25.588 --> 21:26.589
WHAT ABOUT ELVES?

21:26.720 --> 21:27.764
YOU KNOW, LIKE
THE FAIRY TALE?

21:28.591 --> 21:30.811
YOU REMEMBER THE ONE, THE
ONE WHERE THE ELVES COME OUT

21:30.941 --> 21:32.639
AT NIGHT, AND THEY MAKE ALL
THE SHOES FOR THE SHOEMAKER.

21:33.248 --> 21:34.075
-THE ELVES AND
THE SHOEMAKER.

21:34.205 --> 21:35.642
-YOU REMEMBER! [LAUGHS]

21:35.772 --> 21:37.513
MY MOM USED TO TELL ME
THAT STORY EVERY DAY

21:37.644 --> 21:38.993
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE KID AND
SHE'S BRING ME MILK AND COOKIES

21:39.123 --> 21:39.950
AND SHE'D TUCK ME IN AND
I USED TO FEEL SO SAFE!

21:40.081 --> 21:41.430
-CODY.

21:41.561 --> 21:43.693
I THINK YOU'VE BEEN
ON HOLD TOO LONG.

21:44.955 --> 21:45.869
-HELLO!

21:46.609 --> 21:48.176
YES, I AM STILL HERE.

21:48.698 --> 21:49.569
WHAT?

21:50.309 --> 21:51.179
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

21:51.745 --> 21:52.615
WHERE IS IT?

21:53.355 --> 21:54.878
[LAUGHS] I KNOW
EXACTLY WHERE THAT IS!

21:55.009 --> 21:56.489
I'M ON MY WAY.

21:56.619 --> 21:57.838
I KNEW YOU GUYS COULD
DO IT, YOU'RE THE BEST!

21:57.968 --> 21:59.013
[LAUGHS]

21:59.143 --> 22:00.144
THEY FOUND MY BOAT.

22:00.275 --> 22:01.450
-GREAT.

22:01.581 --> 22:04.758
-THEY FOUND
MY BOAT! [CACKLES]

22:06.934 --> 22:08.501
-JUST IN THE
KNICK OF TIME.

22:13.897 --> 22:18.554
-[INTENSE MUSIC]

22:22.253 --> 22:23.342
-HELLO.

22:24.734 --> 22:25.605
EXCUSE ME.

22:26.257 --> 22:27.215
-YEAH, WHAT IS IT?

22:27.781 --> 22:29.652
-YEAH, THE POLICE
SAID MY BOAT WAS HERE.

22:30.392 --> 22:31.306
-NAME?

22:31.437 --> 22:32.351
-MADISON.

22:32.916 --> 22:33.787
-MADISON.

22:33.917 --> 22:35.223
HOW DO YOU SPELL THAT?

22:35.876 --> 22:38.922
-M A D, HEY,

22:39.619 --> 22:40.924
HEY THERE IT IS.

22:41.055 --> 22:42.186
-YEAH THAT'S IT,
THEY JUST TOWED IT IN.

22:42.317 --> 22:43.710
-IT LOOKS FINE!

22:43.840 --> 22:45.451
I THOUGHT WHOEVER STOLE
IT WOULD HAVE REALLY

22:48.279 --> 22:49.455
MESSED IT UP.

22:49.585 --> 22:52.283
-YEAH, THEY PICKED
HER REAL CLEAN.

22:52.936 --> 22:54.938
LIKE A PACK OF VULTURES.

22:58.115 --> 22:59.639
-THINK I'M
GONNA BE SICK.

22:59.769 --> 23:01.945
-EVERY MONTH I GET A COUPLE
OF BOATS JUST LIKE YOURS.

23:02.076 --> 23:04.208
SOME KIND OF RING
OPERATING OUT THERE.

23:05.166 --> 23:07.037
I DON'T SUPPOSE YOU
HAPPENED TO CATCH A GLIMPSE

23:07.168 --> 23:08.561
OF THE BOYS
THAT JACKED YOU?

23:08.691 --> 23:10.345
-NAH, THEY PULLED THE
ANCHOR LINE AND TOOK OFF

23:10.476 --> 23:12.129
BEFORE WE COULD SURFACE.

23:12.260 --> 23:13.392
-COAST GUARD KEEPS SAYING
IF THEY HAD A DESCRIPTION,

23:13.522 --> 23:14.567
THEY MIGHT BE ABLE
TO DO SOMETHING.

23:14.697 --> 23:16.569
-YEAH, WELL I WISH
I COULD HELP THEM.

23:19.093 --> 23:22.052
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK
I SHOULD DO WITH HER?

23:22.792 --> 23:24.359
-WELL I CAN GIVE
YOU AN ESTIMATE

23:24.490 --> 23:25.534
OF ABOUT WHAT IT WOULD COST
TO REPLACE ALL THE GEAR

23:26.317 --> 23:28.798
IF YOU GOT THE
STOMACH FOR IT.

23:30.191 --> 23:33.586
-VERY FUNNY. [SIGHS]

23:36.066 --> 23:37.154
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]

23:43.987 --> 23:45.424
-HI.
-HI, HONEY.

23:45.554 --> 23:47.208
MM, YOU SMELL GOOD.

23:47.338 --> 23:48.949
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

23:49.079 --> 23:51.865
-WELL, WE WENT TO THE
DELI BUT IT WAS TOO CROWDED

23:51.995 --> 23:53.475
SO WE WENT TO KIM LI'S.

23:53.606 --> 23:55.869
DIANE'S NEVER HAD
MONGOLIAN BARBECUE BEFORE.

23:55.999 --> 23:57.479
HERE, IT'S HEAVY.

23:57.610 --> 23:58.437
-HI, MITCH.

23:58.567 --> 23:59.438
-OH, HI, DIANE.

23:59.568 --> 24:01.265
MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME.

24:02.528 --> 24:04.268
-YOU COULD HAVE
STRAIGHTENED UP.

24:04.399 --> 24:06.357
-I DIDN'T THINK YOU'D ACTUALLY
HAVE THE NERVE TO SHOW UP.

24:10.840 --> 24:13.930
-WHAT AN INTERESTING
HOUSE, IT'S SO...

24:14.061 --> 24:14.931
-EARTHY.

24:15.541 --> 24:17.368
-EARTHY? [LAUGHS]

24:18.674 --> 24:20.415
-YOU KNOW ACTUALLY
I'VE BEEN THINKING OF

24:20.546 --> 24:22.025
DOING SOME REDECORATING BUT I
REALLY HAVEN'T HAD A CHANCE.

24:22.156 --> 24:25.115
-OH NO, I WOULDN'T
CHANGE A THING.

24:25.899 --> 24:27.248
I LOVE THE WARMTH AND CHARM.

24:28.902 --> 24:30.686
SO HOW LONG HAVE YOU TWO
BEEN LIVING TOGETHER?

24:31.600 --> 24:33.123
-LIVING TOGETHER?

24:33.733 --> 24:36.475
-WELL TECHNICALLY, I
HAVEN'T REALLY MOVED IN YET.

24:36.605 --> 24:37.388
-NO.

24:37.519 --> 24:39.042
-BUT IT'S JUST THAT

24:39.173 --> 24:39.739
WE SPEND SO
MUCH TIME TOGETHER.

24:39.869 --> 24:40.827
YOU KNOW WE'RE HERE

24:40.957 --> 24:42.785
AND WE'RE AT
THE OFFICE ALL DAY.

24:42.916 --> 24:43.830
-SOMETIMES I WONDER HOW WE
CAN EVEN STAND EACH OTHER.

24:43.960 --> 24:45.048
-OH. [LAUGHS AWKWARDLY]

24:45.179 --> 24:46.615
YOU'RE SO FUNNY.

24:46.746 --> 24:48.399
SWEETHEART, DID YOU
FORGET TO SET THE TABLE?

24:48.530 --> 24:50.750
-OH NO, DARLING,
I DID NOT FORGET.

24:50.880 --> 24:52.665
I WAS BUSY
DOING THE WASH.

24:52.795 --> 24:54.101
BUT I'LL GET RIGHT ON IT.

24:54.231 --> 24:54.710
-ALEX: OKAY.
-MITCH: THANK YOU.

24:54.841 --> 24:55.798
-I'LL HELP.

24:57.147 --> 24:58.714
-YOU KNOW WHAT, WHY DON'T
YOU PUT OUT THE FOOD.

24:58.845 --> 25:00.107
-GREAT.

25:00.237 --> 25:01.108
-AND I WILL OPEN
A BOTTLE OF WINE.

25:02.675 --> 25:03.980
LET'S SEE.

25:04.807 --> 25:06.243
SWEETHEART, WHERE
IS THE CORKSCREW?

25:06.374 --> 25:07.897
-OH, WHERE IT
ALWAYS IS, DARLING.

25:10.291 --> 25:11.858
-MAYBE YOU FORGOT
TO PUT IT BACK.

25:11.988 --> 25:14.687
-NO, ACTUALLY I HAVEN'T
USED IT LATELY, DARLING,

25:14.817 --> 25:16.515
BUT KEEP LOOKING, I'M
SURE YOU'LL FIND IT.

25:16.645 --> 25:18.342
-[WHISPERS] OH COME ON!
DON'T DO THIS TO ME.

25:18.473 --> 25:19.866
-OH, GETTING WARMER.

25:19.996 --> 25:21.955
SEE, THERE IT IS WHERE
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN.

25:22.085 --> 25:25.524
OH LOOK, THE WINE'S
ALREADY OPEN! [LAUGHS]

25:26.525 --> 25:27.656
-ALEX: LET'S HAVE A TOAST.

25:28.309 --> 25:29.876
TO THE HAPPY
BRIDE AND GROOM,

25:30.616 --> 25:31.791
DIANE AND SAM.

25:32.792 --> 25:35.229
EVEN THOUGH SAM CAN'T BE
HERE WITH US IN THE FLESH,

25:35.359 --> 25:37.144
I KNOW HE'S HERE
WITH US IN SPIRIT.

25:37.927 --> 25:38.754
-DIANE: CHEERS.

25:41.670 --> 25:43.803
MM, NICE CHOICE.

25:44.455 --> 25:45.631
-HERE'S TO CHOICES.

25:47.676 --> 25:49.330
-OH, OH NO.

25:49.460 --> 25:51.637
-OH, MY, TOWEL.

25:53.160 --> 25:55.423
-I'M SO CLUMSY,
I'M SO SORRY.

25:56.032 --> 25:57.251
-THERE YOU GO.

25:57.860 --> 25:59.470
-RED WINE STAINS,
DOESN'T IT?

25:59.601 --> 26:00.776
-NOT IF YOU RUN COLD
WATER ON IT RIGHT AWAY.

26:00.907 --> 26:02.299
-RIGHT.
-IT'LL BE FINE.

26:02.430 --> 26:04.040
-WELL I'M AFRAID I DON'T
HAVE ANYTHING TO CHANGE INTO.

26:05.781 --> 26:06.695
OH, ALEX!

26:06.826 --> 26:08.044
YOU WEAR THE SAME SIZE.

26:08.175 --> 26:09.698
YOU MUST HAVE A BLOUSE
I COULD CHANGE INTO.

26:12.135 --> 26:13.833
-I REALLY DON'T HAVE THAT MANY
CLOTHES HERE, I DON'T THINK.

26:13.963 --> 26:15.399
-NO.

26:15.530 --> 26:18.620
-OH, COME ON, YOU PRACTICALLY
LIVE HERE. [LAUGHS]

26:18.751 --> 26:20.927
-YEAH, YOU KNOW
EVERYTHING'S DIRTY,

26:21.057 --> 26:22.319
I REALLY HAVEN'T HAD A CHANCE
TO GO TO THE DRY CLEANERS.

26:22.450 --> 26:23.756
-RIGHT.

26:23.886 --> 26:24.626
WHY DON'T YOU WEAR
ONE OF MY SHIRTS.

26:24.757 --> 26:25.888
-AW.

26:26.019 --> 26:27.411
-THAT IS A GOOD IDEA.

26:27.542 --> 26:28.587
-WHY DON'T YOU SHOW
HERE WHERE THEY ARE?

26:30.153 --> 26:31.372
-OKAY, NO PROBLEM.

26:31.938 --> 26:33.243
LET'S GO.

26:38.640 --> 26:40.076
-IT'S GONNA BE A NIGHT.

26:45.386 --> 26:46.169
YOU WANT A COKE?

26:46.300 --> 26:47.736
-SURE.

26:47.867 --> 26:49.129
-YOU KNOW SHE ISN'T
BUYING A WORD OF THIS.

26:49.259 --> 26:51.000
-WHAT ARE YOU
SAYING, YES SHE IS.

26:51.131 --> 26:52.959
-OH COME ON, SHE SPILT THE
WINE ON HER SHIRT ON PURPOSE.

26:53.089 --> 26:55.178
SHE WAS TESTING YOU AND
YOU FAILED MISERABLY.

26:55.309 --> 26:57.006
-WHAT, BECAUSE I DON'T
HAVE ANY CLOTHES HERE?

26:57.137 --> 26:58.355
-ALEX, IT'S OVER.

26:58.486 --> 26:59.705
LET'S COME CLEAN.

26:59.835 --> 27:01.054
-WE CAN'T DO THAT.

27:01.184 --> 27:02.533
WE'VE ALREADY
TAKEN IT TOO FAR.

27:02.664 --> 27:04.623
-THERE'S ONLY ONE
WAY TO CONVINCE HER.

27:05.275 --> 27:06.494
-DIANE: MITCH?

27:07.147 --> 27:08.409
ALEX?

27:15.416 --> 27:16.417
[CLEARS THROAT]

27:16.547 --> 27:17.723
HEY, HOW'S
THIS SHIRT LOOK?

27:17.853 --> 27:19.159
-OH, DIANE!

27:19.289 --> 27:20.595
I'M SO EMBARRASSED.

27:20.726 --> 27:22.510
-JUST CAN'T KEEP
MY HANDS OFF HER!

27:23.250 --> 27:25.687
-I'M SURE SAM IS THE
SAME WAY WITH YOU.

27:26.340 --> 27:27.863
-NOT REALLY.

27:27.994 --> 27:29.517
-YOU SHOULD SHARE SOME OF
YOUR SEXY SECRETS WITH SAM.

27:29.648 --> 27:32.433
-ENOUGH, YOU ARE
SUCH AN ANIMAL.

27:32.563 --> 27:34.174
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]

27:34.304 --> 27:35.566
-I'LL GET IT!

27:37.699 --> 27:38.613
NEWMAN, HEY.

27:38.744 --> 27:39.614
COME ON IN.

27:39.745 --> 27:40.920
-NO, I CAN'T RIGHT NOW.

27:41.485 --> 27:42.312
MITCH, WHAT'S GOING ON?

27:42.443 --> 27:43.226
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

27:43.357 --> 27:44.445
-YOU FORGOT.

27:44.575 --> 27:46.316
-FORGET WHAT?

27:46.447 --> 27:47.230
-OUR DOUBLE DATE WITH
THE ZIMMERMAN TWINS,

27:47.361 --> 27:48.623
THEY'RE OUT IN THE--

27:48.754 --> 27:50.190
-SH, NEWMAN,
DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

27:50.973 --> 27:51.800
-[DIANE LAUGHS]

27:51.931 --> 27:53.193
-THE ZIMMERMAN TWINS?

27:53.323 --> 27:54.629
-YES, THE ZIMMERMAN TWINS.

27:54.760 --> 27:55.891
COME ON, WE CAN'T
KEEP THEM WAITING.

27:56.022 --> 27:58.372
-UM, I'M SORRY BUDDY
BUT I REALLY CAN'T.

27:58.502 --> 28:00.940
SEE, ALEX AND I WERE
HAVING DINNER HERE

28:01.070 --> 28:03.159
AND DIANE WAS HERE AND SHE
SPILLED SOME WINE ON HER,

28:03.290 --> 28:04.770
THAT'S WHY SHE'S WEARING
ONE OF MY SHIRTS,

28:04.900 --> 28:06.206
BUT I REALLY, I CAN'T.

28:06.336 --> 28:08.208
[SIGHS]

28:12.560 --> 28:13.779
I GOTTA GO!

28:15.302 --> 28:16.172
BOTH OF THEM?

28:16.303 --> 28:17.391
-YES, BOTH.

28:17.521 --> 28:18.348
-HOW'D YOU
PULL THIS OFF?

28:19.045 --> 28:20.829
-[SIGH] WOW.

28:32.711 --> 28:37.672
-[CONCERNED MUSIC]

28:41.720 --> 28:42.721
-HI.

28:46.768 --> 28:47.769
HEY.

28:51.904 --> 28:54.123
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?

28:56.996 --> 28:58.301
HI.

28:58.432 --> 28:59.999
-[GRUNTS]

29:00.129 --> 29:01.087
-COME HERE.

29:01.217 --> 29:02.044
IT'S ALRIGHT.

29:02.175 --> 29:03.045
-[GRUNTS]

29:03.176 --> 29:04.612
-IT'S OKAY, COME HERE.

29:04.743 --> 29:05.700
SWEETIE.

29:07.397 --> 29:08.747
WAIT A SECOND!

29:09.748 --> 29:10.574
COME HERE!

29:10.705 --> 29:12.011
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

29:13.447 --> 29:14.927
HEY.

29:15.057 --> 29:16.493
WHY ARE YOU
RUNNING AWAY?

29:18.539 --> 29:19.975
ARE YOU OKAY?

29:22.717 --> 29:24.675
I JUST WANT TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT YOUR SANDCASTLES.

29:24.806 --> 29:26.460
I THINK THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.

29:48.699 --> 29:50.223
-HEY, WHAT THE
HELL GOING ON, HUH?

29:51.137 --> 29:52.660
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
GET OFF MY BOAT!

29:52.791 --> 29:54.357
-[GRUNTS]

29:54.488 --> 29:56.403
-WHOA!

29:59.232 --> 30:01.277
-HEY FORGET ABOUT THAT
THING, LET'S GET OUT OF HERE!

30:04.324 --> 30:07.283
-HEY, THAT'S MY BOAT!

30:07.414 --> 30:11.331
-[ACTION MUSIC]

30:26.868 --> 30:28.391
-[WHISTLES]

30:28.522 --> 30:29.871
OVER HERE!

30:36.835 --> 30:37.748
HEY!

30:38.924 --> 30:39.838
I'M HERE.

30:48.063 --> 30:50.065
HEY, MAN, SOMEBODY
STOLE MY BOAT.

30:50.196 --> 30:51.327
-THEY STOLE YOUR BOAT?

30:51.458 --> 30:52.894
AND WENT WHERE?

30:53.025 --> 30:53.895
-RIGHT OVER THERE
ABOUT 10 MINUTES AGO.

30:54.026 --> 30:55.070
-GET ON.

30:55.201 --> 30:56.593
NEWMIE, I THINK
WE HAVE OUR BOYS!

30:56.724 --> 31:00.597
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

31:15.177 --> 31:19.181
-[PEOPLE CHATTER]

31:29.496 --> 31:32.716
-[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

31:55.261 --> 31:56.044
-HI.

31:56.175 --> 31:56.958
-HEY.

31:57.089 --> 31:57.959
WHO WAS THAT?

31:58.090 --> 31:59.178
YOU OKAY?

32:00.570 --> 32:04.487
-THAT WAS A VERY
UNFORTUNATE LITTLE BOY.

32:05.662 --> 32:08.665
HE'S GOT A DISEASE CALLED
XERODERMA PIGMENTOSUM,

32:08.796 --> 32:11.146
WHICH BASICALLY MEANS HE
CAN NEVER GO OUT IN THE SUN.

32:13.670 --> 32:15.672
-HE WAS THE ONE BUILDING
THE SANDCASTLES, HUH?

32:17.283 --> 32:19.981
-FELL ASLEEP LAST NIGHT
WAITING FOR THE TIDE TO GO OUT

32:20.112 --> 32:23.898
WHEN I FOUND HIM THIS MORNING,
RIGHT AFTER THE SUN CAME UP.

32:24.029 --> 32:26.988
HE ALREADY HAD BLISTERS
COVERING HIS FACE.

32:28.163 --> 32:29.425
SO SAD.

32:31.384 --> 32:33.560
CAN YOU IMAGINE
LIVING LIKE THAT?

32:34.474 --> 32:36.955
MAKES YOU REALIZE HOW
MUCH WE TAKE FOR GRANTED.

32:38.130 --> 32:39.261
-YEAH.

32:39.392 --> 32:40.523
NO KIDDING.

32:44.832 --> 32:46.268
-ALEX!

32:49.358 --> 32:50.533
-SAM!

32:50.664 --> 32:51.926
HI!

32:53.275 --> 32:55.016
I THOUGHT YOU WEREN'T
GONNA BE HERE 'TIL FRIDAY.

32:55.147 --> 32:56.844
-DIDN'T YOU GET ME
MESSAGES, MY EMAIL?

32:56.975 --> 32:58.019
-NO.

32:58.628 --> 32:59.542
ARE YOU ALRIGHT?

32:59.673 --> 33:01.109
-NO, I'M NOT ALRIGHT.

33:01.240 --> 33:03.459
YOU REALIZE DIANE HAS
CALLED OFF THE WEDDING?

33:03.590 --> 33:04.808
-WHAT?

33:04.939 --> 33:09.291
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

33:11.467 --> 33:13.339
-[SIGHS]

33:29.398 --> 33:30.486
-I THINK I SEE THEM,

33:30.617 --> 33:31.792
THEY'RE A HALF
MILE DEAD AHEAD.

33:37.667 --> 33:39.626
-LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE HEADING
RIGHT FOR THE MARINA, NEWMIE.

33:39.756 --> 33:41.019
-WE CAN CATCH
THEM, LET'S GO!

33:42.150 --> 33:43.543
CAN'T THIS THING
GO ANY FASTER?

33:50.028 --> 33:51.855
-MAN, I'M RUNNING
OUT OF GAS.

33:51.986 --> 33:53.596
I'M GONNA TAKE
IT DOWN A NOTCH.

33:54.684 --> 33:56.686
-[SIREN]

33:56.817 --> 33:57.774
-DAMMIT IT'S THE LIFEGUARD!

33:57.905 --> 33:58.732
WE GOTTA MAKE A RUN FOR IT!

33:58.862 --> 34:00.342
GIVE IT EVERYTHING WE GOT!

34:00.473 --> 34:02.170
-[ENGINE REVS]

34:04.172 --> 34:06.696
-RESCUE THREE TO
295, COME IN 295.

34:06.827 --> 34:08.916
-WALKIE: YEAH
RESCUE THREE WE COPY.

34:09.047 --> 34:10.483
WHAT'S UP, CODY?

34:10.612 --> 34:12.614
-WE ARE IN PURSUIT OF A
STOLEN VESSEL HEADING SOUTH,

34:12.746 --> 34:14.400
SOUTHWEST FROM POINT BERMAN.

34:14.530 --> 34:17.272
PLEASE ALERT THE COAST
GUARD AND HARBOR PATROL.

34:17.402 --> 34:19.579
I HAVE A FEELING THEY MAY
WANNA CHAT WITH THESE BOYS.

34:19.708 --> 34:20.710
-WALKIE: ROGER.

34:20.841 --> 34:24.062
-[ACTION MUSIC]

34:24.192 --> 34:27.021
-[SIREN]

34:27.630 --> 34:29.850
-ALRIGHT, NEWMIE, GET ME
AS CLOSE AS YOU CAN, MAN.

34:29.980 --> 34:31.112
-WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

34:32.112 --> 34:34.637
-YOU DON'T ASK,
I WON'T TELL.

34:36.422 --> 34:39.728
-[ACTION MUSIC]

34:41.427 --> 34:42.862
-CODY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

34:42.993 --> 34:44.560
COME ON, GET DOWN.

34:49.174 --> 34:51.784
-NEWMIE, GET ME AS
CLOSE AS YOU CAN!

34:53.656 --> 34:57.791
-[ACTION MUSIC]

35:03.840 --> 35:05.581
-LITTLE TIGHTER, NEWMIE!

35:07.888 --> 35:09.237
COME ON, GET CLOSER.

35:24.078 --> 35:25.427
[GRUNTS]

35:50.235 --> 35:52.889
-[ENGINE SPUTTERS]

36:02.551 --> 36:03.683
-WHEW!

36:05.946 --> 36:07.077
WOO HOO!

36:07.600 --> 36:09.515
[PANTS]

36:17.131 --> 36:19.307
[LAUGHS HYSTERICALLY]

36:26.923 --> 36:28.534
-CUT THAT PRETTY
CLOSE THERE, BIG GUY.

36:28.664 --> 36:31.058
-NEVER THOUGHT I WOULD BE
SO HAPPY TO RUN OUT OF GAS

36:31.189 --> 36:32.190
IN MY LIFE.

36:32.799 --> 36:34.192
-I GOT SOMETHING
YOU MAY NEED.

36:40.589 --> 36:41.547
-GIVE ME A HAND, NEWMIE.

36:41.677 --> 36:42.939
-ALRIGHT, COMING OVER.

36:43.070 --> 36:44.941
-HEY, THANKS A LOT, MAN.

36:54.037 --> 36:55.343
-DIANE.

36:55.474 --> 36:56.823
-HI, MITCH.

36:56.953 --> 36:57.998
-ALRIGHT, LOOK.
-I NEED TO TELL YOU THAT.

36:58.128 --> 36:59.869
-[BOTH LAUGH]

37:01.523 --> 37:04.091
-[SIGHS] I NEED TO APOLOGIZE

37:04.222 --> 37:06.006
FOR DISRUPTING YOUR LIFE
THE PAST COUPLE OF DAYS.

37:06.136 --> 37:08.051
-YOU DON'T HAVE
TO APOLOGIZE.

37:08.182 --> 37:09.705
-YES, I DO.

37:11.141 --> 37:12.404
YOU'RE A VERY NICE PERSON,

37:12.534 --> 37:14.449
AND I THINK YOU
DESERVE AN EXPLANATION

37:14.580 --> 37:17.931
FOR MY RATHER
BIZARRE BEHAVIOR.

37:18.061 --> 37:20.629
-DIANE, EVERYBODY
ACTS A LITTLE BIZARRE

37:20.760 --> 37:22.240
RIGHT BEFORE
THEY GET MARRIED.

37:22.370 --> 37:23.719
I MEAN COME ON, YOU'RE
INSECURE, YOU'RE ANXIOUS.

37:23.850 --> 37:25.155
-UNBALANCED.

37:25.286 --> 37:26.113
-SOMETIMES.

37:26.244 --> 37:29.986
-[LAUGHS] NO, REALLY.

37:31.684 --> 37:32.728
I'M SORRY.

37:32.859 --> 37:35.209
AND I HOPE YOU
CAN FORGIVE ME

37:35.340 --> 37:37.559
FOR EVERYTHING.

37:37.690 --> 37:39.039
-IT'S OKAY.

37:40.214 --> 37:42.216
-I'LL NEVER FORGET
YOU, MITCH BUCHANAN.

37:45.088 --> 37:46.481
-I'LL NEVER
FORGET YOU EITHER.

37:46.612 --> 37:48.004
-[LAUGHS]

37:48.135 --> 37:49.789
-HEY, SEE YOU
AT THE WEDDING.

37:49.919 --> 37:51.530
-I'LL BE IN WHITE.

37:52.835 --> 37:57.623
-[CALM MUSIC]

38:03.106 --> 38:05.500
-WAIT, WAIT, HOW FAR
AWAY IS THIS TOWER?

38:05.631 --> 38:06.849
-FIVE MINUTES
IN THE TRUCK.

38:06.980 --> 38:08.024
-AND WHAT DOES
THIS MITCH GUY

38:08.155 --> 38:09.461
HAVE TO DO WITH
DIANE, ANYWAY?

38:09.591 --> 38:11.724
-LOOK, I WILL EXPLAIN
EVERYTHING, OKAY?

38:12.681 --> 38:13.595
-OKAY.

38:13.726 --> 38:15.336
DIANE!

38:15.467 --> 38:16.685
-SAM!

38:16.816 --> 38:18.687
[SQUEALS]

38:20.210 --> 38:21.342
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE HERE!

38:21.473 --> 38:22.952
-OF COURSE I'M HERE.

38:23.083 --> 38:25.041
BABY, I CAN'T LET YOU
CALL OFF THE WEDDING.

38:25.172 --> 38:26.391
I LOVE YOU.

38:27.043 --> 38:28.654
-I LOVE YOU TOO, SAM.

38:29.307 --> 38:31.134
-WHAT WAS THAT
MESSAGE ALL ABOUT?

38:32.571 --> 38:34.616
-OH, THAT WAS JOKE.

38:35.313 --> 38:36.488
-SAM: A JOKE?

38:38.446 --> 38:40.448
-YEAH, ALEX SAID YOU
LIKED PRACTICAL JOKES.

38:41.319 --> 38:42.581
-YOU DID?

38:42.711 --> 38:46.062
-WELL, YOU KNOW, MAYBE I
SAID IT IN CONVERSATION.

38:46.193 --> 38:48.543
-I HATE PRACTICAL JOKES!

38:48.674 --> 38:50.937
YOU'VE TAKEN 10
YEARS OFF MY LIFE.

38:51.764 --> 38:56.638
BABY IN THE FUTURE, NEVER
BELIEVE A WORD SHE SAYS, OKAY?

38:57.509 --> 38:58.771
-I PROMISE YOU I WON'T.

38:58.901 --> 38:59.989
-OH, BABY.

39:01.121 --> 39:01.904
-I LOVE YOU!

39:02.035 --> 39:03.297
-I LOVE YOU, TOO.

39:05.299 --> 39:06.822
-[DIANE GIGGLING]

39:08.824 --> 39:13.133
-[SWEET MUSIC]

39:38.201 --> 39:40.029
-HEY, RYKER, I'VE BEEN
LOOKING ALL OVER FOR YOU.

39:40.160 --> 39:41.204
COOL WEDDING, HUH?

39:41.335 --> 39:42.597
-YEAH.

39:42.728 --> 39:43.903
-OH, WHAT'S WRONG?

39:44.033 --> 39:45.383
WHY SO SENTIMENTAL?

39:47.123 --> 39:49.517
-YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW IF
IT'S BECAUSE I FEEL HAPPY

39:49.648 --> 39:53.173
FOR SAM AND DIANE, OR I
FEEL SAD FOR THE LITTLE BOY

39:53.303 --> 39:54.870
WHO BUILT
THESE SANDCASTLES.

39:55.001 --> 39:56.742
-WELL I THOUGHT YOU WERE
TRYING TO RAISE MONEY

39:56.872 --> 39:58.091
FOR THE CURE,
WHAT'S IT CALLED?

39:58.221 --> 39:59.919
-XERODERMA PIGMENTOSUM.

40:00.049 --> 40:00.920
YEAH, I AM.

40:01.050 --> 40:02.617
-WELL, THAT'S
NOT BAD THING.

40:03.183 --> 40:05.054
TRYING TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE
IN SOMEONE'S LIFE.

40:05.185 --> 40:06.404
IT'S A GOOD THING.

40:06.969 --> 40:08.057
USUALLY.

40:08.188 --> 40:10.233
-[SIGHS] I SURE HOPE SO.

40:10.886 --> 40:13.672
-SO, NICE CATCH OF
THE BOUQUET, HUH?

40:13.802 --> 40:15.195
-WHAT DO YOU
MEAN NICE CATCH,

40:15.325 --> 40:17.066
SHE THREW IT AT ME.

40:17.197 --> 40:20.069
I MEAN, CAN'T REALLY DUCK WHEN
IT'S AT POINT BLANK RANGE.

40:20.896 --> 40:23.508
YOU NEVER TOLD ME HOW
YOU FINALLY GOT DIANE

40:23.638 --> 40:24.422
TO GIVE UP ON YOU.

40:24.552 --> 40:25.771
-DIDN'T DO A THING,

40:25.901 --> 40:26.772
SHE JUST FINALLY
CAME TO YOUR SENSES.

40:27.686 --> 40:29.296
-SHE PROBABLY REALIZED
THAT SHE COULDN'T COMPETE

40:29.427 --> 40:32.081
WITH YOUR ENDLESS SUPPLY
OF ZIMMERMAN TWINS.

40:32.212 --> 40:34.257
-EITHER THAT
OR SHE REALIZED

40:34.388 --> 40:35.781
THAT SAM'S A
REALLY SPECIAL GUY.

40:36.346 --> 40:37.478
-YEAH, HE IS.

40:38.174 --> 40:39.262
YOU KNOW WHAT, BUCHANAN?

40:39.393 --> 40:40.263
SO ARE YOU.

40:41.003 --> 40:43.745
IN YOUR OWN
INIMITABLE WAY.

40:44.964 --> 40:46.574
THANKS FOR BEING
SUCH A GOOD FRIEND.

40:49.838 --> 40:52.145
-YOU KNOW,
SPEAKING OF FRIENDS.

40:53.189 --> 40:54.364
THE OTHER NIGHT.

40:55.322 --> 40:57.455
DO YOU ALWAYS KISS
YOUR FRIENDS LIKE THAT?

40:58.064 --> 40:58.891
-NO.

40:59.021 --> 40:59.892
I WAS JUST ACTING.

41:00.022 --> 41:00.893
-REALLY.

41:01.023 --> 41:02.198
-YEAH.

41:02.329 --> 41:03.765
-YOU SURE THAT'S
ALL IT WAS,

41:03.896 --> 41:05.854
BECAUSE I KIND OF FELT
SOME SPARKS OR SOMETHING.

41:06.638 --> 41:09.510
-I ASSURE YOU,
IT WAS ALL AN ACT.

41:09.641 --> 41:11.251
-HI, MITCH!

41:11.381 --> 41:13.209
-HEY, MITCH,
LOOK WHO I GOT.

41:13.340 --> 41:14.384
-DON'T TELL ME.

41:14.515 --> 41:15.647
THE ZIMMERMAN TWINS?

41:15.777 --> 41:17.997
-YOU'RE RIGHT,
IT WAS ALL AN ACT.

41:18.127 --> 41:19.868
-BUCHANAN WHERE
ARE YOU GOING,

41:19.999 --> 41:21.479
YOU CAN'T JUST TAKE OFF.

41:21.609 --> 41:23.263
-TELL SAM AND DIANE I
SAID CONGRATULATIONS,

41:23.393 --> 41:25.091
HAVE A GREAT LIFE AND SAVE A
PIECE OF WEDDING CAKE FOR ME.

41:25.221 --> 41:26.745
NEWMIE, LET'S GO, BABY!

41:26.875 --> 41:27.746
-BUCHANAN!

41:27.876 --> 41:29.356
-RYKER!

41:44.850 --> 41:49.245
-[END THEME PLAYING]
